Having grown up in an apartment, I can give you some hints.  We used to
take old coils which had fine wire in them and go up on the roof of the
apartment and unwind the coil slowly.  Since it was very thin wire, no one
saw it.  Then when it passed by our window on the first floor, we would pull
it in.  Up top we would attach the wire to anything convenient and we were
off and running and no one saw it.  Illegal?  Yes, but invisible too.  Do
such antennas work?  You would be amazed what 65 feet of wire can do on all
frequencies despite the lack of precision cutting of lengths.  And we used
the steam pipes as a ground too.
