That is generally correct. However in true "3-piece" baseboard, the cap
protrudes well beyond the rectangular section and makes the toe
necessary to prevent straight-legged furniture from bunging the cap.
With the modern 2-piece base, the rectangular section is the limiting
dimension, the cap carving does not protrude. Also modern base is
usually 1" (3/4 finished) stock and so the profile is much thinner
overall. Our baseboard is a full 1-3/4" thick with 5/4 (1" net) base
and 1" (3/4 net) toe molding. Most modern systems net out at 1-1/4"
overall.

Peter Wieck
Wyncote, PA
